sec.p:
‭חשרגנו‬ (BDB-1951), ‘cast out, drive out, expelled’ (Ugaritic /g-r-š/;
        Sumerian riši). This verb describes movement away from an original
        position/state.

fn.p:
Radine, The Book of Amos in Emergent Judah, pp. 142–43. Lament for Sumer
          and Ur (LSUr) 31–37, 71, 153, 184, 446; cf. exile themes in Amos 4.2–3; 5.5, 27; 6.7;
          7.17; 9.4).

A. Lo, Job 28 as Rhetoric in the Context of Job 22–31 (VTSup, 97;
          Leiden: Brill, 2002). Lo cites Hartley, Habel, Westermann, Newsom, all of whom view Job
          9.5–13 as a single ‘hymn’, pp. 133–40.
